Yeh table software engineering me **Defect Repair Ratio** dikhata hai.
Iska matlab hai ki agar software me bug/error jaldi pakda jaye toh usko fix karna sasta hota hai, aur late pakda jaye toh bahut mehenga padta hai.

Table ka meaning:

| Phase          | Ratio | Meaning                                                                     |
| -------------- | ----- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Analysis       | 1     | Agar requirement phase me bug mil gaya toh cost sabse kam                   |
| Design         | 10    | Design phase me same bug fix karne ki cost 10 times ho jati hai             |
| Implementation | 100   | Coding/testing ke baad bug mile toh fix karna 100 times costly ho sakta hai |

Example:

Maan lo requirement me mistake thi:

* Analysis phase me fix cost = ₹100
* Design phase me wahi fix = ₹1000
* Implementation phase me wahi fix = ₹10000

Reason:
Kyuki baad me fix karne par:

* code change karna padta hai
* testing dobara hoti hai
* documentation update hoti hai
* kabhi pura module bhi rewrite karna padta hai

Simple line me:

> “Earlier the defect is found, cheaper it is to fix.”

Isliye software development me:

* proper analysis
* requirement checking
* early testing
  bahut important hote hain.
